# When ever writing a function you should ALWAYS have a docstring

## This is a good example of a docstring

```python
def exampleFunction(param1, param2=42):
    """
    Brief one-line summary of the function.

    More detailed explanation of the function, its purpose, and any background
    information or side effects. This can span multiple lines.

    Parameters
    ----------
    param1 : type
        Description of the first parameter.
    param2 : type, optional
        Description of the second parameter (default is 42).

    Returns
    -------
    return_type
        Description of what is returned.

    Raises
    ------
    ExceptionType
        Description of the exception and the condition under which it is raised.

    Examples
    --------
    >>> example_function('hello')
    'Processed: hello'

    Notes
    -----
    Additional information about the implementation, limitations, or references.
    """
    pass
```